ndex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 07, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ubb1665702556881.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ubb1665702556881.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ubb1665702556881.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ubb1665702556881\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Field Interface Codes \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__field_interface_codes_360552\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A field interface code is specified in the field's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Interface</span> property, and determines how the data is stored in the database. The code defines the packing code and field length, as well numeric decimal and scaling options.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__topic_d111683e1_d111684e1_d111685e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__p_d111686e1_d111687e1_d111688e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PackingCode</var>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Length</var>}{<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>}{<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">TotalLength</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">V</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldId</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">SubfieldId</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">Separator</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__p_d111689e1_d111690e1_d111691e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">I8.4</code> (8-byte integer, scaled to 4 decimal places)</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__section_w2043ab1b5b5_w2044ab1b5_w2045ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Syntax for Field Interface Definitions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n Code\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PackingCode</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">Packing code, such as C, B2, M2, I8, W*. For\n                        more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uww1665702531035.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uww1665702531035.html\" title=\"Packing codes are mappings between Uniface data types and DBMS data types (storage formats). When writing a field, Uniface passes the data and a valid packing code to the DBMS connector, which uses the packing code to determine the appropriate storage format for storing the data in the target DBMS. Packing codes also determine how data is interfaced with 3GL routines.\">Packing Codes</a>. <p class=\"p\">Packing codes\n                           determine how the data should be presented to the DBMS connector for\n                           packing and storing in the DBMS.</p> Some packing codes are\n                        associated with a default field layout. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sfb1665702556960.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sfb1665702556960.html\" title=\"If no packing code or field interface code is defined in the Database Interface for a field, Uniface uses a default packing code based on the data type. Some packing codes are also associated with a default display format.\">Default Packing Codes and Display Formats per Data Type</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Length</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Length of each subfield in the field. If subfields are not defined, <var class=\"keyword varname\">Length</var> is the total field length.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">.n</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Optional decimal point and scaling.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">TotalLength</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Total length of field if subfields are defined.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">V</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Constant that indicates where the variable part of the definition begins.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Type</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Variable-length identifier type.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldId</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Field identifier.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">SubfieldId</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n First subfield identifier.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Separator</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ubb1665702556881__table_d13067e1_d13068e1_d13069e1__entry__2\">\n Subfield separator.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yyf1665702556802.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Interface (Fields)</a><p>This property (also known as the field interface) determines how data in the field is physically stored in the database.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Field Interface Codes Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 07, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Field Interface Codes A field interface code is specified in the field's Database Interface property, and determines how the data is stored in the database. The code defines the packing code and field length, as well numeric decimal and scaling options. PackingCode { Length }{ . n }{ ( TotalLength ) } V Type / FieldId / SubfieldId / Separator Example: I8.4 (8-byte integer, scaled to 4 decimal places) Table 1. Syntax for Field Interface Definitions Code Meaning PackingCode Packing code, such as C, B2, M2, I8, W*. For more information, see Packing Codes . Packing codes determine how the data should be presented to the DBMS connector for packing and storing in the DBMS. Some packing codes are associated with a default field layout. For more information, see Default Packing Codes and Display Formats per Data Type . Length Length of each subfield in the field. If subfields are not defined, Length is the total field length. .n Optional decimal point and scaling. TotalLength Total length of field if subfields are defined. V Constant that indicates where the variable part of the definition begins. Type Variable-length identifier type. FieldId Field identifier. SubfieldId First subfield identifier. Separator Subfield separator. Related Links Database Interface (Fields) This property (also known as the field interface) determines how data in the field is physically stored in the database. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}